.TH "pci_read_legacy_io" 9 "pci_read_legacy_io" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_read_legacy_io \- read byte(s) from legacy I/O port space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" pci_read_legacy_io
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "struct kobject *kobj "  ","
.BI "struct bin_attribute *bin_attr "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "loff_t off "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
open sysfs file
.IP "kobj" 12
kobject corresponding to file to read from
.IP "bin_attr" 12
struct bin_attribute for this file
.IP "buf" 12
buffer to store results
.IP "off" 12
offset into legacy I/O port space
.IP "count" 12
number of bytes to read
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reads 1, 2, or 4 bytes from legacy I/O port space using an arch specific
callback routine (pci_legacy_read).
